  "verificationNotes": "CORRECTED: archClass changed from 'moe' to 'dense' and archDisplay rewritten \u2014 the official Gemini 1.5 technical report (Section 3.2 and Appendix 12.1 Model Card, Table 45) explicitly states 'Gemini 1.5 Flash is a dense Transformer based model that is online distilled ... from Gemini 1.5 Pro,' in direct contrast to 1.5 Pro which IS described as sparse MoE. Downloaded and text-extracted the full 154-page PDF report directly (prior fetch attempts were rate-limited/binary-blocked) and verbatim-confirmed all 9 result rows against Table 11 and Table 22. Release date (I/O, May 14 2024), 1M context, and '100+ languages' (developers.googleblog.com) also confirmed. Pricing ($0.075/$0.30 per 1M tokens, <=128K) confirmed as the Aug 2024 price-cut rate, matching the record."
